<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ANTILOCK BRAKES/TRACTION CONTROL: MERITOR WABCO WITH "D" VERSION ECU - AUTOMATIC TRACTION CONTROL (ATC) -
        ATC COMPONENTS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
        <title>ATC COMPONENTS</title>
        <para>ATC may be used with individual ABS modulator valves, or with the ABS Valve Package. When installed with
            individual ABS modulator valves, an ATC solenoid valve is mounted on the frame or crossmember, near the rear
            of the vehicle. When it is part of the ABS valve package, an ATC valve is attached to the relay valve.
        </para>
        <para>A cable connects the ECU to the ATC valve.</para>
        <para>ATC components are illustrated in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0403715">Figure 15</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0403715" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg04/g0403715.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                     scalefitheight="312px"/>
            <caption>Figure 15. ATC Components</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
